# Primary Button Usage Guidelines

To maintain consistent branding and user experience across the application, follow these guidelines for primary action buttons:

## 1. Use GoldButton for Primary Actions

Always use `GoldButton` (imported from `$lib/components/app/gold-button.svelte`) for the primary Call-To-Action (CTA) on any page or form.
Avoid using the raw Shadcn `Button` component with custom styling or other custom buttons for primary actions.

### Correct Usage:
```svelte
<script lang="ts">
	import GoldButton from '$lib/components/app/gold-button.svelte';
</script>

<GoldButton onclick={handleClick}>
	Acquire Now
</GoldButton>
```

## 2. Component Design & Props

`GoldButton` wraps the Shadcn `Button` component and inherits all `ButtonProps` (e.g., `disabled`, `type`, `size`, etc.), ensuring it is fully compatible.

- Custom classes can be passed using the standard Svelte 5 `class` property if minor layout adjustments are needed.
- Use `Snippet` children for content.
